  "prompt": "What is the value of [math]\\sqrt [i\\pi ] {-1}[/math]?",
  "response": "To evaluate the expression \\( \\sqrt[i\\pi]{-1} \\), we begin by rewriting it in exponential form. The expression can be rewritten as:\n\n\\[\n-1 = e^{i\\pi}\n\\]\n\nsince \\( -1 \\) is represented by \\( e^{i\\pi} \\) in the complex exponential form. We aim to find \\( \\sqrt[i\\pi]{-1} \\), which can be expressed as:\n\n\\[\n(-1)^{\\frac{1}{i\\pi}} = \\left( e^{i\\pi} \\right)^{\\frac{1}{i\\pi}}\n\\]\n\nUsing the properties of exponents, we simplify this as follows:\n\n\\[\n\\left( e^{i\\pi} \\right)^{\\frac{1}{i\\pi}} = e^{\\frac{i\\pi}{i\\pi}} = e^1 = e\n\\]\n\nThus, we have:\n\n\\[\n\\sqrt[i\\pi]{-1} = e\n\\]\n\nIn conclusion, the value of \\( \\sqrt[i\\pi]{-1} \\) is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{e}\n\\]",
